<p itemprop="description">Consultancy involves providing expert advice, guidance and recommendations to help organisations solve problems, improve performance, and achieve their objectives through structured analysis and stakeholder engagement.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can understand the role of consultancy in problem-solving and recognise when expert advice is needed to address organisational challenges.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can provide basic advice and recommendations based on analysis, and support consultancy engagements by gathering information and presenting findings.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can lead consultancy engagements, structure complex problems, develop evidence-based recommendations, and influence stakeholders to adopt solutions.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can establish consultancy approaches and methodologies, lead complex organisational transformation as a trusted advisor, and mentor others in consultancy skills.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

